            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This one caught my eye and I've been looking into this. I noticed that `parser_gc` doesn't null out the userdata pointer after `ts_parser_delete`:\n\n```c\nstatic int parser_gc(lua_State *L)\n{\n  TSParser *p = parser_check(L, 1);\n  logger_gc(ts_parser_logger(p));\n  ts_parser_delete(p);\n  return 0;  // *ud still points to freed memory\n}\n```\n\nThis means if the finalizer runs at an unexpected time (as the stack trace suggests - GC firing inside `nvim_buf_get_lines`), and anything touches the userdata afterwards, we'd get exactly this crash.\n\nDo you have steps to reproduce? I'd like to dig deeper into this and confirm the cause.",
